The gods here who have temples are Artemis called the Bearer of children, and Dionysus, and Æsculapius.
The statues of Æsculapius and Dionysus are of stone, and there is a brazen statue of Zeus Soter in the marketplace.
There is also a brazen statue of Athene in the citadel in the open air, with a crow in her hand.
I also saw the tomb of Epime- lides.
Why they call the harbour the harbour of the' Achæans I do not know.
As you go on about 80 stades from Corone you come to a temple of Apollo, near the sea, which is held in high honour :
according to the Messenian tradition it is the most ancient of all Apollo's temples, and the god heals diseases.
They call the god Corydus.
